<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span lang=IT
style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-ansi-language:IT'>Spiegazioni
dell'esercitazione del 3 Giugno 2004<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=IT
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Scopo dell’esercitazione</span></b><span lang=IT
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>: scopo dell’esercitazione è di completare ed
animare un versione stilizzata ma abbastanza completa di un robot con tutti i
principali punti di snodo e che includa le due mani. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=IT
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Nota bene: </span></b><span lang=IT
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Tutte le operazioni di disegno e di modifica delle
matrici devono (preferibilmente) essere effettuate nella Display Function,
chiamata <i>disegna</i> nel nostro caso. Nelle altre funzioni, dovete soltanto
cambiare i valori dei parametri che vengono usati dalla Display Function.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:
IT'>Cose da fare:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>1)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Copiate in
una vostra directory i files Mano.c, Mano.h, robot.c presenti sia sul sito Web
che contenuti nella directory del corso in Laboratorio con l’esercitazione di
oggi <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:18.0pt;text-align:justify'><span lang=IT
style='mso-ansi-language:IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>2)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Avviate il
Visual C++, caricate il file robot.c, compilatelo ed eseguitelo. Notate che il
file Mano.h viene incluso e di conseguenza viene caricato Mano.c<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:
IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:36.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list 36.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>3)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>Analizzate
il codice di robot.c e cercate di comprenderne il funzionamento. Sono definiti
seguenti tasti per l’interazione: <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘z’ per
allontanarsi (aumenta la variabile <i>distanza</i>)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘Z’ per
avvicinarsi (diminuisce la variabile <i>distanza</i>)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘w’ passa
dalla modalità solida a quella wireframe (solo contorno)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘ ‘ (spazio)
ruota il robot sull’asse y<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘+’ aumenta
la velocità dell’animazione (incrementa <i>FPS</i>)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:72.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:
-18.0pt;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo3;tab-stops:list 72.0pt'><![if !supportLists]><span
lang=IT style='font-family:Symbol;mso-ansi-language:IT'>·<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:IT'>‘-’
diminuisce la velocità dell’animazione (decrementa <i>FPS</i>)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=IT style='mso-ansi-language:
IT'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

